<style>
  body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      height: 100vh;
  }

  .keyboard-container {
      flex-grow: 1;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: flex-end;
      padding: 10px;
  }

  .key {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      height: 50px;
      min-width: 30px;
      margin: 4px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 4px;
      background-color: #f7f7f7;
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
      transition: background-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .key.wide {
      flex: 1;
  }

  .key.space {
      min-width: 200px; /* Adjust space bar width as needed */
      flex: none;
  }

  .key.enter {
      min-width: 90px; /* Adjust enter key width as needed */
  }

  .key:hover {
      background-color: #e0e0e0;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .output {
      width: calc(100% - 20px);
      height: 80px;
      margin: 10px;
      padding: 10px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 16px;
      resize: none;
  }

  /* Responsive adjustments */
  @media (max-height: 500px), (max-width: 500px) {
      .key {
          height: 40px;
          min-width: 25px;
          margin: 2px;
      }
      .output {
          height: 60px;
      }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<textarea id="output" class="output" placeholder="Type here or use the virtual keyboard..."></textarea>
<div class="keyboard-container" id="keyboard"></div>

<script>
  const keys = [
      ['1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7', '8', '9', '0', '-', '='],
      ['q', 'w', 'e', 'r', 't', 'y', 'u', 'i', 'o', 'p', '[', ']', '\\'],
      ['a', 's', 'd', 'f', 'g', 'h', 'j', 'k', 'l', ';', '\''],
      ['z', 'x', 'c', 'v', 'b', 'n', 'm', ',', '.', '/'],
      ['Space', 'Enter', 'Backspace']
  ];

  const outputElement = document.getElementById("output");
  const keyboardContainer = document.getElementById("keyboard");

  keys.forEach(row => {
      row.forEach(key => {
          const keyElement = document.createElement("button");
          keyElement.textContent = key;
          keyElement.className = "key";

          if (key === "Space") {
              keyElement.className += " wide space";
          } else if (key === "Enter" || key === "Backspace") {
              keyElement.className += " wide " + key.toLowerCase();
          }

          keyElement.addEventListener("click", () => {
              const cursorPos = outputElement.selectionStart;
              const textBefore = outputElement.value.slice(0, cursorPos);
              const textAfter = outputElement.value.slice(cursorPos);

              if (key === "Space") {
                  outputElement.value = textBefore + " " + textAfter;
                  outputElement.selectionStart = cursorPos + 1;
                  outputElement.selectionEnd = cursorPos + 1;
              } else if (key === "Enter") {
                  outputElement.value = textBefore + "\n" + textAfter;
                  outputElement.selectionStart = cursorPos + 1;
                  outputElement.selectionEnd = cursorPos + 1;
              } else if (key === "Backspace") {
                  if (outputElement.selectionStart === outputElement.selectionEnd) {
                      // No text is selected; remove character before the cursor
                      outputElement.value = textBefore.slice(0, -1) + textAfter;
                      outputElement.selectionStart = cursorPos - 1;
                      outputElement.selectionEnd = cursorPos - 1;
                  } else {
                      // Text is selected; remove it
                      outputElement.value = textBefore + textAfter;
                      outputElement.selectionStart = cursorPos;
                      outputElement.selectionEnd = cursorPos;
                  }
              } else {
                  outputElement.value = textBefore + key + textAfter;
                  outputElement.selectionStart = cursorPos + key.length;
                  outputElement.selectionEnd = cursorPos + key.length;
              }
              outputElement.focus();
          });

          keyboardContainer.appendChild(keyElement);
      });
  });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

In this updated example, the `keys` array is laid out in the way a physical keyboard would be, with each inner array representing a row of keys. The JavaScript code generates a `button` for each key and adds them to the `.keyboard-container`. The styles have been updated to make the keys responsive, with visual feedback (press effect) included. The `.wide` class adds extra width to the `Enter`, `Backspace`, and `Space` keys. The `space` class, in particular, is applied to the space bar key to give it significant width.

The event listener on each key button updates the `.output` textarea with the corresponding character when a key is pressed, simulates the `Space`, `Enter`, and `Backspace` functionality, and maintains cursor position correctly.

This setup simulates a simple on-screen keyboard for both desktop and mobile web browsers. Remember that in a real-world application, there are considerations for browser compatibility, keyboard accessibility, and security for user input.

